Vendored tools — bundled into the macOS app alongside scripts/.

exiftool   Perl script + lib/ from Image-ExifTool distribution (exiftool.org).
           Currently v13.50. To update: download a new tar.gz, replace
           exiftool and lib/.

jetlag-metadata
           Swift CLI wrapping ExifTool with a JSON-in/JSON-out interface.
           Source at macos/Sources/Tools/jetlag-metadata/. Build:
             cd macos/Sources/Tools/jetlag-metadata && swift build -c release
             cp .build/release/jetlag-metadata ../../../../scripts/tools/
           The binary is gitignored — each developer builds locally.

tag        macOS Finder tag CLI (github.com/jdberry/tag), MIT licensed.
           Source vendored at tag-src/. Build on macOS:
             scripts/tools/build-tag.sh
           Or copy from Homebrew:
             cp $(brew --prefix)/bin/tag scripts/tools/tag
           The built binary is gitignored — each developer builds locally.

ffprobe    Stream inspection tool from the FFmpeg project (ffmpeg.org).
           Used by generate-gyroflow.py to detect gyro/motion data streams.
           Download a static build:
             scripts/tools/download-ffprobe.sh
           Or copy from Homebrew:
             cp $(brew --prefix)/bin/ffprobe scripts/tools/ffprobe
           The binary is gitignored — each developer downloads locally.

gyroflow   Gyroflow CLI (gyroflow.xyz), used for .gyroflow project generation.
           The Gyroflow app binary doubles as a CLI (accepts --export-project).
           Download or extract from an existing install:
             scripts/tools/download-gyroflow.sh
           The script checks /Applications/Gyroflow.app, Homebrew, then
           downloads from GitHub releases.
           The binary is gitignored — each developer downloads locally.
